<?xml version="1.0" encoding="utf-8" standalone="yes"?><rss version="2.0" xmlns:atom="http://www.w3.org/2005/Atom"><channel><title>Value on ErrorCode — Error Code Reference &amp; Solutions</title><link>https://errorcode.excellentwiki.com/tags/value/</link><description>Recent content in Value on ErrorCode — Error Code Reference &amp; Solutions</description><generator>Hugo</generator><language>en</language><atom:link href="https://errorcode.excellentwiki.com/tags/value/index.xml" rel="self" type="application/rss+xml"/><item><title>[Solution] C++ std::bad_optional_access - empty optional</title><link>https://errorcode.excellentwiki.com/languages/cpp/bad-optional-access/</link><pubDate>Mon, 01 Jan 0001 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate><guid>https://errorcode.excellentwiki.com/languages/cpp/bad-optional-access/</guid><description>&lt;h1 id="stdbad_optional_access---empty-optional"&gt;std::bad_optional_access - empty optional&lt;/h1&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;code&gt;std::bad_optional_access&lt;/code&gt; is thrown when you call &lt;code&gt;std::optional::value()&lt;/code&gt; on an empty optional.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h2 id="common-causes"&gt;Common Causes&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;div class="highlight"&gt;&lt;pre tabindex="0" style="color:#f8f8f2;background-color:#272822;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4;-webkit-text-size-adjust:none;"&gt;&lt;code class="language-cpp" data-lang="cpp"&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;// Cause 1: value() on empty optional
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;std&lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;::&lt;/span&gt;optional&lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;&amp;lt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;int&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;&amp;gt;&lt;/span&gt; opt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;int&lt;/span&gt; val &lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;=&lt;/span&gt; opt.value(); &lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;// throws
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;// Cause 2: * operator on empty optional
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;std&lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;::&lt;/span&gt;optional&lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;&amp;lt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;int&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;&amp;gt;&lt;/span&gt; opt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;int&lt;/span&gt; val &lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;=&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;*&lt;/span&gt;opt; &lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;// undefined behavior
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;// Cause 3: Optional not set conditionally
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;std&lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;::&lt;/span&gt;optional&lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;&amp;lt;&lt;/span&gt;std&lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;::&lt;/span&gt;string&lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;&amp;gt;&lt;/span&gt; name;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;if&lt;/span&gt; (condition) {
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt; name &lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;=&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#e6db74"&gt;&amp;#34;Alice&amp;#34;&lt;/span&gt;;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;}
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;std&lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;::&lt;/span&gt;string n &lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;=&lt;/span&gt; name.value(); &lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;// throws if condition was false
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;h2 id="how-to-fix"&gt;How to Fix&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;h3 id="fix-1-check-has_value"&gt;Fix 1: Check has_value()&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;div class="highlight"&gt;&lt;pre tabindex="0" style="color:#f8f8f2;background-color:#272822;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4;-webkit-text-size-adjust:none;"&gt;&lt;code class="language-cpp" data-lang="cpp"&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;std&lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;::&lt;/span&gt;optional&lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;&amp;lt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;int&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;&amp;gt;&lt;/span&gt; opt &lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;=&lt;/span&gt; get_value();
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;if&lt;/span&gt; (opt.has_value()) {
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;int&lt;/span&gt; val &lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;=&lt;/span&gt; opt.value();
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;}
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;h3 id="fix-2-use-value_or"&gt;Fix 2: Use value_or()&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;div class="highlight"&gt;&lt;pre tabindex="0" style="color:#f8f8f2;background-color:#272822;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4;-webkit-text-size-adjust:none;"&gt;&lt;code class="language-cpp" data-lang="cpp"&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;int&lt;/span&gt; val &lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;=&lt;/span&gt; opt.value_or(&lt;span style="color:#ae81ff"&gt;0&lt;/span&gt;); &lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;// returns 0 if empty
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;h3 id="fix-3-use-operator-with-check"&gt;Fix 3: Use operator* with check&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;div class="highlight"&gt;&lt;pre tabindex="0" style="color:#f8f8f2;background-color:#272822;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4;-webkit-text-size-adjust:none;"&gt;&lt;code class="language-cpp" data-lang="cpp"&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;if&lt;/span&gt; (opt) {
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;int&lt;/span&gt; val &lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;=&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;*&lt;/span&gt;opt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;}
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;h2 id="related-errors"&gt;Related Errors&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;a href="https://errorcode.excellentwiki.com/languages/cpp/bad-variant-access/"&gt;std::bad_variant_access&lt;/a&gt; — wrong variant type.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;a href="https://errorcode.excellentwiki.com/languages/cpp/any-cast-error/"&gt;std::bad_any_cast&lt;/a&gt; — any_cast failure.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;a href="https://errorcode.excellentwiki.com/languages/cpp/bad-function-call/"&gt;std::bad_function_call&lt;/a&gt; — empty function.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;</description></item><item><title>[Solution] Go Reflect Value.Type on Zero Value Fix</title><link>https://errorcode.excellentwiki.com/languages/go/reflect-type-2/</link><pubDate>Mon, 01 Jan 0001 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate><guid>https://errorcode.excellentwiki.com/languages/go/reflect-type-2/</guid><description>&lt;h1 id="reflect-valuetype-on-zero-value-fix"&gt;Reflect Value.Type on Zero Value Fix&lt;/h1&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The &lt;code&gt;reflect: call of reflect.Value.Type on zero Value&lt;/code&gt; error occurs when calling &lt;code&gt;.Type()&lt;/code&gt; on an invalid &lt;code&gt;reflect.Value&lt;/code&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h2 id="description"&gt;Description&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;code&gt;reflect.Value&lt;/code&gt; is a struct that wraps a value and its type information. An &amp;ldquo;invalid&amp;rdquo; or &amp;ldquo;zero&amp;rdquo; &lt;code&gt;reflect.Value&lt;/code&gt; is returned by operations that don&amp;rsquo;t have a value (like &lt;code&gt;reflect.ValueOf(nil)&lt;/code&gt; or accessing a non-existent map element). Calling &lt;code&gt;.Type()&lt;/code&gt; on an invalid &lt;code&gt;reflect.Value&lt;/code&gt; panics because there is no type to report.&lt;/p&gt;</description></item><item><title>[Solution] Go Reflect Zero Value Error Fix</title><link>https://errorcode.excellentwiki.com/languages/go/reflect-type/</link><pubDate>Mon, 01 Jan 0001 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate><guid>https://errorcode.excellentwiki.com/languages/go/reflect-type/</guid><description>&lt;h1 id="reflect-call-of-reflectvaluetype-on-zero-value--fix"&gt;Reflect: Call of reflect.Value.Type on Zero Value — Fix&lt;/h1&gt;
&lt;p&gt;A &amp;ldquo;reflect: call of reflect.Value.Type on zero Value&amp;rdquo; error occurs when you call methods on a zero &lt;code&gt;reflect.Value&lt;/code&gt; — typically from &lt;code&gt;reflect.ValueOf(nil)&lt;/code&gt; or an unset &lt;code&gt;reflect.Value&lt;/code&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h2 id="description"&gt;Description&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Go&amp;rsquo;s &lt;code&gt;reflect&lt;/code&gt; package represents values as &lt;code&gt;reflect.Value&lt;/code&gt;. A zero &lt;code&gt;reflect.Value&lt;/code&gt; (the default value, or from reflecting on &lt;code&gt;nil&lt;/code&gt;) doesn&amp;rsquo;t hold any value. Calling methods like &lt;code&gt;.Type()&lt;/code&gt;, &lt;code&gt;.Kind()&lt;/code&gt;, or &lt;code&gt;.Interface()&lt;/code&gt; on it causes a panic.&lt;/p&gt;</description></item><item><title>[Solution] PowerShell ArgumentException in PowerShell</title><link>https://errorcode.excellentwiki.com/languages/powershell/powershell-argument-error/</link><pubDate>Mon, 01 Jan 0001 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate><guid>https://errorcode.excellentwiki.com/languages/powershell/powershell-argument-error/</guid><description>&lt;h1 id="powershell-argumentexception-fix"&gt;PowerShell ArgumentException Fix&lt;/h1&gt;
&lt;p&gt;ArgumentExceptions occur when a method or cmdlet receives an argument that doesn&amp;rsquo;t meet its expected type, range, or format requirements.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h2 id="what-this-error-means"&gt;What This Error Means&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;.NET methods and PowerShell cmdlets validate their arguments. An ArgumentException means the value is within the correct type but outside the valid range or doesn&amp;rsquo;t meet constraints.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h2 id="common-causes"&gt;Common Causes&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Numeric value out of allowed range&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;String value doesn&amp;rsquo;t match expected format (e.g., path, regex)&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Null passed where a non-null value is required&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Enum value not in the allowed set&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Collection count doesn&amp;rsquo;t match expected size&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;h2 id="how-to-fix"&gt;How to Fix&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;h3 id="1-validate-argument-ranges"&gt;1. Validate argument ranges&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;div class="highlight"&gt;&lt;pre tabindex="0" style="color:#f8f8f2;background-color:#272822;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4;-webkit-text-size-adjust:none;"&gt;&lt;code class="language-powershell" data-lang="powershell"&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;# Check parameter constraints&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;Get-Help Some-Command -Parameter ParameterName
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;# Example: port must be 1-65535&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;$port = &lt;span style="color:#ae81ff"&gt;99999&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;# ArgumentException&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;$port = &lt;span style="color:#ae81ff"&gt;8080&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;# Valid&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;h3 id="2-check-argument-type"&gt;2. Check argument type&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;div class="highlight"&gt;&lt;pre tabindex="0" style="color:#f8f8f2;background-color:#272822;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4;-webkit-text-size-adjust:none;"&gt;&lt;code class="language-powershell" data-lang="powershell"&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;# Verify type matches&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;$value.GetType()
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;# Convert if needed&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;$number = [&lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;int&lt;/span&gt;]&lt;span style="color:#e6db74"&gt;&amp;#34;42&amp;#34;&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;# String to int&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;$date = [&lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;DateTime&lt;/span&gt;]&lt;span style="color:#e6db74"&gt;&amp;#34;2024-01-01&amp;#34;&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;# String to DateTime&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;h3 id="3-handle-null-values"&gt;3. Handle null values&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;div class="highlight"&gt;&lt;pre tabindex="0" style="color:#f8f8f2;background-color:#272822;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4;-webkit-text-size-adjust:none;"&gt;&lt;code class="language-powershell" data-lang="powershell"&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;# WRONG: null argument&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;$nullValue = $null
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;[&lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;System.IO.File&lt;/span&gt;]::ReadAllText($nullValue)
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;# RIGHT: validate first&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;if&lt;/span&gt; ($null &lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;-ne&lt;/span&gt; $path &lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;-and&lt;/span&gt; (Test-Path $path)) {
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt; [&lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;System.IO.File&lt;/span&gt;]::ReadAllText($path)
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;}
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;h3 id="4-use-valid-enum-values"&gt;4. Use valid enum values&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;div class="highlight"&gt;&lt;pre tabindex="0" style="color:#f8f8f2;background-color:#272822;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4;-webkit-text-size-adjust:none;"&gt;&lt;code class="language-powershell" data-lang="powershell"&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;# Check allowed values&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;[&lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;enum&lt;/span&gt;]::GetValues([&lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;System.ConsoleColor&lt;/span&gt;])
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;# Use valid value&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;[&lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;Console&lt;/span&gt;]::ForegroundColor = [&lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;ConsoleColor&lt;/span&gt;]::Red &lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;# Valid&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;h2 id="related-errors"&gt;Related Errors&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;a href="powershell-type-error"&gt;Type Mismatch&lt;/a&gt; — type conversion errors&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;a href="powershell-parameter-binding"&gt;ParameterBindingException&lt;/a&gt; — parameter issues&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;a href="invalid-operation"&gt;InvalidOperation&lt;/a&gt; — operation errors&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;</description></item><item><title>[Solution] Rust Use of Moved Value — Compiler Error Fix</title><link>https://errorcode.excellentwiki.com/languages/rust/move-error/</link><pubDate>Mon, 01 Jan 0001 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate><guid>https://errorcode.excellentwiki.com/languages/rust/move-error/</guid><description>&lt;h1 id="use-of-moved-value--compiler-error"&gt;Use of Moved Value — Compiler Error&lt;/h1&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The error &lt;code&gt;use of moved value&lt;/code&gt; occurs when you attempt to use a value after it has been moved to another owner. In Rust, moving a value transfers ownership, and the original variable can no longer be accessed.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h2 id="description"&gt;Description&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Rust&amp;rsquo;s ownership system ensures that each value has exactly one owner. When you assign a value to another variable or pass it to a function, ownership is transferred (moved) unless the type implements the &lt;code&gt;Copy&lt;/code&gt; trait. After a move, the original variable is considered invalid.&lt;/p&gt;</description></item><item><title>[Solution] Rust Use of Moved Value — Move Error</title><link>https://errorcode.excellentwiki.com/languages/rust/move/</link><pubDate>Mon, 01 Jan 0001 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate><guid>https://errorcode.excellentwiki.com/languages/rust/move/</guid><description>&lt;h1 id="use-of-moved-value--move-error"&gt;Use of Moved Value — Move Error&lt;/h1&gt;
&lt;p&gt;A compiler error with the message &amp;ldquo;use of moved value&amp;rdquo; occurs when you try to use a value after it has been moved to another variable or function. In Rust, assigning a value to another variable or passing it to a function by default moves ownership.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h2 id="description"&gt;Description&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Rust&amp;rsquo;s ownership system ensures memory safety without a garbage collector. When you assign a value like &lt;code&gt;let b = a&lt;/code&gt;, the value is &lt;em&gt;moved&lt;/em&gt; from &lt;code&gt;a&lt;/code&gt; to &lt;code&gt;b&lt;/code&gt;. After the move, &lt;code&gt;a&lt;/code&gt; is no longer valid. This prevents double-free errors and ensures each value has exactly one owner.&lt;/p&gt;</description></item><item><title>[Solution] Rust Use of Moved Value — Value Moved Error</title><link>https://errorcode.excellentwiki.com/languages/rust/move-2/</link><pubDate>Mon, 01 Jan 0001 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate><guid>https://errorcode.excellentwiki.com/languages/rust/move-2/</guid><description>&lt;h1 id="use-of-moved-value--value-moved-error"&gt;Use of Moved Value — Value Moved Error&lt;/h1&gt;
&lt;p&gt;A compiler error with the message &amp;ldquo;use of moved value&amp;rdquo; occurs when you try to use a variable after its value has been moved to another owner.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h2 id="description"&gt;Description&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;In Rust, assigning a value to a new variable or passing it to a function by value &lt;em&gt;moves&lt;/em&gt; ownership. The original variable becomes invalid. This prevents double-free bugs without a garbage collector. Types implementing &lt;code&gt;Copy&lt;/code&gt; (integers, bools) are copied instead of moved.&lt;/p&gt;</description></item><item><title>[Solution] Scala Value Is Not a Member Error</title><link>https://errorcode.excellentwiki.com/languages/scala/scala-value-not-a-member/</link><pubDate>Mon, 01 Jan 0001 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate><guid>https://errorcode.excellentwiki.com/languages/scala/scala-value-not-a-member/</guid><description>&lt;h2 id="what-this-error-means"&gt;What This Error Means&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The error &lt;code&gt;value X is not a member of Y&lt;/code&gt; occurs when you try to access a method or field that doesn&amp;rsquo;t exist on a type. This is a compile-time error indicating the type doesn&amp;rsquo;t have the requested member.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h2 id="common-causes"&gt;Common Causes&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Typo in method or field name&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Missing import for extension methods&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Wrong type (accessing members of wrong class)&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Method exists in different version of library&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Implicit conversions not available&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;h2 id="how-to-fix"&gt;How to Fix&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;div class="highlight"&gt;&lt;pre tabindex="0" style="color:#f8f8f2;background-color:#272822;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4;-webkit-text-size-adjust:none;"&gt;&lt;code class="language-scala" data-lang="scala"&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;// WRONG: Typo in method name
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;val&lt;/span&gt; list &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;=&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#a6e22e"&gt;List&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;(&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#ae81ff"&gt;1&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;,&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#ae81ff"&gt;2&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;,&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#ae81ff"&gt;3&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;)&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;list&lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;.&lt;/span&gt;lenght &lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;// Error: value &amp;#39;lenght&amp;#39; is not a member of List[Int]
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;// CORRECT: Use correct method name
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;list&lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;.&lt;/span&gt;length
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div class="highlight"&gt;&lt;pre tabindex="0" style="color:#f8f8f2;background-color:#272822;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4;-webkit-text-size-adjust:none;"&gt;&lt;code class="language-scala" data-lang="scala"&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;// WRONG: Missing import for extension method
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;val&lt;/span&gt; result &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;=&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#e6db74"&gt;&amp;#34;hello&amp;#34;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;.&lt;/span&gt;reverse &lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;// May need import
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;// CORRECT: Import required implicit conversions
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;import&lt;/span&gt; scala.collection.JavaConverters._
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;// Or for newer Scala:
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;import&lt;/span&gt; scala.jdk.CollectionConverters._
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div class="highlight"&gt;&lt;pre tabindex="0" style="color:#f8f8f2;background-color:#272822;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4;-webkit-text-size-adjust:none;"&gt;&lt;code class="language-scala" data-lang="scala"&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;// WRONG: Accessing member on wrong type
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;case&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;class&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#a6e22e"&gt;Person&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;(&lt;/span&gt;name&lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;:&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;String&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;,&lt;/span&gt; age&lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;:&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;Int&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;)&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;val&lt;/span&gt; person &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;=&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#a6e22e"&gt;Person&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;(&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#e6db74"&gt;&amp;#34;Alice&amp;#34;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;,&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#ae81ff"&gt;30&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;)&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;person&lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;.&lt;/span&gt;salary &lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;// Error: value &amp;#39;salary&amp;#39; is not a member of Person
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;// CORRECT: Check available members
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;// Use IDE auto-complete or documentation
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;person&lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;.&lt;/span&gt;name &lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;// &amp;#34;Alice&amp;#34;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;person&lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;.&lt;/span&gt;age &lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;// 30
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div class="highlight"&gt;&lt;pre tabindex="0" style="color:#f8f8f2;background-color:#272822;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4;-webkit-text-size-adjust:none;"&gt;&lt;code class="language-scala" data-lang="scala"&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;// WRONG: Accessing package member without import
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;val&lt;/span&gt; result &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;=&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#a6e22e"&gt;Duration&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;.&lt;/span&gt;fromNanos&lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;(&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#ae81ff"&gt;1000&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;)&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;// Error without import
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;// CORRECT: Import the package
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;import&lt;/span&gt; scala.concurrent.duration._
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;val&lt;/span&gt; result &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;=&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#a6e22e"&gt;Duration&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;.&lt;/span&gt;fromNanos&lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;(&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#ae81ff"&gt;1000&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;)&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;h2 id="examples"&gt;Examples&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;div class="highlight"&gt;&lt;pre tabindex="0" style="color:#f8f8f2;background-color:#272822;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4;-webkit-text-size-adjust:none;"&gt;&lt;code class="language-scala" data-lang="scala"&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;// Example 1: Find available members
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;// In REPL, type: val x = List(1,2,3)
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;// Then type: x. and press Tab to see all members
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;// Example 2: Extension methods pattern
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;implicit&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;class&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#a6e22e"&gt;StringOps&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;(&lt;/span&gt;s&lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;:&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;String&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;)&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;{&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;def&lt;/span&gt; isPalindrome&lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;:&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;Boolean&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;=&lt;/span&gt; s &lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;==&lt;/span&gt; s&lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;.&lt;/span&gt;reverse
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;}&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#e6db74"&gt;&amp;#34;racecar&amp;#34;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;.&lt;/span&gt;isPalindrome &lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;// true
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;// Example 3: Check library documentation
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;// val r = scala.util.Random
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;// r.nextInt // Available
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;// r.nextString // Check if available in your version
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;h2 id="related-errors"&gt;Related Errors&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;a href=""&gt;scala-type-mismatch&lt;/a&gt; — type mismatch&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;a href="https://errorcode.excellentwiki.com/languages/scala/scala-implicit-not-found/"&gt;scala-implicit-not-found&lt;/a&gt; — implicit not found&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;a href="https://errorcode.excellentwiki.com/languages/scala/scala-not-type/"&gt;scala-not-type&lt;/a&gt; — not a type error&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;</description></item><item><title>[Solution] TypeScript TS2693 — 'X' only refers to a type</title><link>https://errorcode.excellentwiki.com/languages/typescript/ts2693-x-only-referenced/</link><pubDate>Mon, 01 Jan 0001 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate><guid>https://errorcode.excellentwiki.com/languages/typescript/ts2693-x-only-referenced/</guid><description>&lt;h1 id="ts2693--x-only-refers-to-a-type-but-is-being-used-as-a-value-here"&gt;TS2693 — &amp;lsquo;X&amp;rsquo; only refers to a type but is being used as a value here&lt;/h1&gt;
&lt;p&gt;TS2693 occurs when you try to use a type-only declaration as a runtime value. Types exist only at compile time and cannot be used at runtime.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h2 id="common-causes"&gt;Common Causes&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;div class="highlight"&gt;&lt;pre tabindex="0" style="color:#f8f8f2;background-color:#272822;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4;-webkit-text-size-adjust:none;"&gt;&lt;code class="language-typescript" data-lang="typescript"&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;// Cause 1: Using interface as value
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;interface&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#a6e22e"&gt;User&lt;/span&gt; {
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#a6e22e"&gt;name&lt;/span&gt;: &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;string&lt;/span&gt;;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;}
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;const&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#a6e22e"&gt;u&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;=&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;new&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#a6e22e"&gt;User&lt;/span&gt;(); &lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;// TS2693: &amp;#39;User&amp;#39; only refers to a type
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;// Cause 2: Using type alias as value
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;type&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#a6e22e"&gt;Point&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;=&lt;/span&gt; { &lt;span style="color:#a6e22e"&gt;x&lt;/span&gt;: &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;number&lt;/span&gt;; &lt;span style="color:#a6e22e"&gt;y&lt;/span&gt;: &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;number&lt;/span&gt; };
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;const&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#a6e22e"&gt;p&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;=&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#a6e22e"&gt;Point&lt;/span&gt;(); &lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;// TS2693
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;// Cause 3: Importing type as value
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;import&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;type&lt;/span&gt; { &lt;span style="color:#a6e22e"&gt;Config&lt;/span&gt; } &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;from&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#e6db74"&gt;&amp;#34;./config&amp;#34;&lt;/span&gt;;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;const&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#a6e22e"&gt;c&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;=&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;new&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#a6e22e"&gt;Config&lt;/span&gt;(); &lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;// TS2693: Config is type-only
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;h2 id="how-to-fix"&gt;How to Fix&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;h3 id="fix-1-use-class-instead-of-interface"&gt;Fix 1: Use class instead of interface&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;div class="highlight"&gt;&lt;pre tabindex="0" style="color:#f8f8f2;background-color:#272822;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4;-webkit-text-size-adjust:none;"&gt;&lt;code class="language-typescript" data-lang="typescript"&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;class&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#a6e22e"&gt;User&lt;/span&gt; {
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#a6e22e"&gt;name&lt;/span&gt;: &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;string&lt;/span&gt;;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;constructor&lt;/span&gt;(&lt;span style="color:#a6e22e"&gt;name&lt;/span&gt;: &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;string&lt;/span&gt;) {
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;this&lt;/span&gt;.&lt;span style="color:#a6e22e"&gt;name&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;=&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#a6e22e"&gt;name&lt;/span&gt;;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt; }
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;}
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;const&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#a6e22e"&gt;u&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;=&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;new&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#a6e22e"&gt;User&lt;/span&gt;(&lt;span style="color:#e6db74"&gt;&amp;#34;Alice&amp;#34;&lt;/span&gt;);
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;h3 id="fix-2-use-typeof-for-type-operations"&gt;Fix 2: Use typeof for type operations&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;div class="highlight"&gt;&lt;pre tabindex="0" style="color:#f8f8f2;background-color:#272822;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4;-webkit-text-size-adjust:none;"&gt;&lt;code class="language-typescript" data-lang="typescript"&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;const&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#a6e22e"&gt;obj&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;=&lt;/span&gt; { &lt;span style="color:#a6e22e"&gt;x&lt;/span&gt;: &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;1&lt;/span&gt;, &lt;span style="color:#a6e22e"&gt;y&lt;/span&gt;: &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;2&lt;/span&gt; };
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;type&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#a6e22e"&gt;Point&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;=&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;typeof&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#a6e22e"&gt;obj&lt;/span&gt;; &lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;// type from value
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;h3 id="fix-3-import-as-value"&gt;Fix 3: Import as value&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;div class="highlight"&gt;&lt;pre tabindex="0" style="color:#f8f8f2;background-color:#272822;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4;-webkit-text-size-adjust:none;"&gt;&lt;code class="language-typescript" data-lang="typescript"&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;import&lt;/span&gt; { &lt;span style="color:#a6e22e"&gt;Config&lt;/span&gt; } &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;from&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#e6db74"&gt;&amp;#34;./config&amp;#34;&lt;/span&gt;; &lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;// remove &amp;#39;type&amp;#39;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;const&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#a6e22e"&gt;c&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;=&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;new&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#a6e22e"&gt;Config&lt;/span&gt;();
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;h2 id="related-errors"&gt;Related Errors&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;a href="https://errorcode.excellentwiki.com/languages/typescript/ts2339-property-access/"&gt;TS2339: Property is type-only import&lt;/a&gt; — type-only import access.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;a href="https://errorcode.excellentwiki.com/languages/typescript/ts2304-cannot-find/"&gt;TS2304: Cannot find name&lt;/a&gt; — undefined identifier.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;a href="https://errorcode.excellentwiki.com/languages/typescript/ts2349-not-callable/"&gt;TS2349: This expression is not callable&lt;/a&gt; — non-callable expression.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;</description></item><item><title>[Solution] Python ValueError — Invalid Argument Fix</title><link>https://errorcode.excellentwiki.com/languages/python/valueerror/</link><pubDate>Mon, 01 Jan 0001 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate><guid>https://errorcode.excellentwiki.com/languages/python/valueerror/</guid><description>&lt;h1 id="valueerror--invalid-argument-fix"&gt;ValueError — Invalid Argument Fix&lt;/h1&gt;
&lt;p&gt;A &lt;code&gt;ValueError&lt;/code&gt; is raised when a function receives an argument of the correct type but an inappropriate value. Unlike &lt;code&gt;TypeError&lt;/code&gt;, the types match — the data itself is invalid.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h2 id="description"&gt;Description&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;code&gt;ValueError&lt;/code&gt; occurs across many standard library functions:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;code&gt;int(&amp;quot;&amp;quot;)&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/strong&gt; — cannot convert an empty string to an integer.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;code&gt;int(&amp;quot;abc&amp;quot;)&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/strong&gt; — non-numeric string passed to &lt;code&gt;int()&lt;/code&gt;.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;code&gt;json.loads(&amp;quot;&amp;quot;)&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/strong&gt; — empty string is not valid JSON.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;code&gt;float(&amp;quot;inf&amp;quot;)&lt;/code&gt; might be unexpected&lt;/strong&gt; — depending on context, special floats can cause downstream issues.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;code&gt;math.sqrt(-1)&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/strong&gt; — negative input to a function that only accepts non-negative values.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;code&gt;open()&lt;/code&gt; with bad mode&lt;/strong&gt; — invalid mode string.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The key distinction: the function signature accepts the type, but the value violates the function&amp;rsquo;s preconditions.&lt;/p&gt;</description></item></channel></rss>